## Running the data set: 

```{r, eval=FALSE,echo=TRUE}
library(dplyr)
movies<- read.csv("movies.csv")
glimpse(movies)
```
## Topic to explore: What makes a successful movie?

```{r, eval=FALSE,echo=TRUE}
# Relationship of IMDB user score with runtime  
ggplot(movies, aes (x=score,
                      y=runtime)) +
      geom_point()+
  facet_wrap(~genre, ncol=5)
```
Note that the `echo = FALSE` parameter was added to the code chunk to prevent printing of the R code that generated the plot.

```{r, eval=FALSE,echo=TRUE}
# filter dataset into 3 main companies 

paramount <- movies %>% filter(company=="Paramount Pictures")
warner <- movies %>% filter(company=="Warner Bros.")
universal <- movies %>% filter(company=="Universal Pictures")

glimpse(paramount)
```

